WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.458 --> 00:00:14.375
-[praying indistinctly]
-[mystical music playing]

2
00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:22.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

3
00:00:30.625 --> 00:00:32.791
-…please help us.
-Mom. are you all right?

4
00:00:34.375 --> 00:00:39.416
[telephone ringing]

5
00:00:39.541 --> 00:00:43.250
[exhales] No.
but the remedy will be here soon.

6
00:00:45.791 --> 00:00:47.416
[telephone continues ringing]

7
00:00:47.500 --> 00:00:49.000
Yes. birds.

8
00:00:50.625 --> 00:00:52.791
That's right.
I'll get many birds.

9
00:00:53.583 --> 00:00:57.041
How can you possibly think about that
when he knocked your teeth out?

10
00:00:59.500 --> 00:01:00.916
-No more moping around.
-[groans]

11
00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:02.666
We've been holed up in here too long.

12
00:01:05.250 --> 00:01:07.375
Do you smell that? Flowers?

13
00:01:08.458 --> 00:01:09.375
Violet.

14
00:01:11.833 --> 00:01:12.958
[Blanca groans]

15
00:01:13.041 --> 00:01:15.625
[telephone continues ringing]

16
00:01:16.458 --> 00:01:17.583
Old bastard.

17
00:01:19.125 --> 00:01:22.166
[Alba] <i>In the house. nobody ever mentioned</i>
 <i>what my grandpa had done.</i>

18
00:01:22.791 --> 00:01:26.000
 <i>And that secret was kept.</i>
 <i>like many others. in the life diaries.</i>

19
00:01:29.791 --> 00:01:30.708
Mom.

20
00:01:31.625 --> 00:01:32.708
Are you feeling better?

21
00:01:32.791 --> 00:01:34.375
I'm better. Yes. better.

22
00:01:37.000 --> 00:01:38.791
[Alba] <i>After those first weeks.</i>

23
00:01:38.875 --> 00:01:42.416
 <i>my grandma concluded that</i>
 <i>her patience for misfortune had run out.</i>

24
00:01:46.791 --> 00:01:47.875
We have arrived.

25
00:01:47.958 --> 00:01:49.708
Clara. We are here to help. honey.

26
00:01:54.958 --> 00:01:55.916
-Finally.
-Thank you

27
00:02:00.833 --> 00:02:02.833
Children. Come here.

28
00:02:02.916 --> 00:02:04.708
Meet the Mora sisters. my friends.

29
00:02:04.791 --> 00:02:07.083
This is Luisa. Nora and Marta.

30
00:02:07.166 --> 00:02:08.458
[Blanca] Your astral sisters?

31
00:02:08.916 --> 00:02:10.833
Indeed. And you…

32
00:02:13.125 --> 00:02:14.500
my precious girl.

33
00:02:15.625 --> 00:02:18.583
you'll stop thinking
that you deserve what happened to you.

34
00:02:19.375 --> 00:02:20.291
Stop it.

35
00:02:22.041 --> 00:02:22.958
Yeah?

36
00:02:23.041 --> 00:02:24.875
[telephone ringing]

37
00:02:25.916 --> 00:02:27.041
Come in. I'll show you.

38
00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:29.416
They are both lovely.

39
00:02:29.500 --> 00:02:30.625
-[Clara] Mm.
-[Marta] Yes.

40
00:02:32.875 --> 00:02:34.416
[mystical music playing]

41
00:02:34.500 --> 00:02:35.416
[Nora] Here it is.

42
00:02:36.916 --> 00:02:38.125
Here it was.

43
00:02:39.250 --> 00:02:40.708
And here it will be.

44
00:02:41.791 --> 00:02:43.291
This place was waiting for us.

45
00:02:43.375 --> 00:02:44.291
-Yes.
-It was.

46
00:02:45.333 --> 00:02:47.250
-Thank you for coming.
-Oh.

47
00:02:47.416 --> 00:02:49.458
[all exclaiming softly]

48
00:02:52.166 --> 00:02:53.083
Now…

49
00:02:55.833 --> 00:02:56.750
it's done.

50
00:02:58.750 --> 00:03:01.583
[mystical music continues]

51
00:03:05.125 --> 00:03:06.583
Can you sense the energy?

52
00:03:07.583 --> 00:03:08.500
No.

53
00:03:11.041 --> 00:03:11.958
You will soon.

54
00:03:14.625 --> 00:03:15.541
[Blanca] Mmm.

55
00:03:16.125 --> 00:03:17.916
Excuse me.
I have to go study.

56
00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:20.000
You're going to get admitted
to medical school.

57
00:03:20.083 --> 00:03:21.166
Don't worry about it.

58
00:03:21.250 --> 00:03:22.541
[Jaime chuckles softly]

59
00:03:22.791 --> 00:03:25.458
Thank you for the news.
but I better not get cocky about it.

60
00:03:25.541 --> 00:03:27.458
[Luisa shushes] There's…

61
00:03:28.541 --> 00:03:31.333
there's a…
an overwhelming love.

62
00:03:32.958 --> 00:03:34.625
A restless creek.

63
00:03:37.958 --> 00:03:39.250
Don't worry. child.

64
00:03:45.250 --> 00:03:48.916
Listen. this cycle needs to be brought
to an end so another can begin.

65
00:03:50.541 --> 00:03:51.708
It's gonna be a girl

66
00:03:52.875 --> 00:03:55.041
but only if you decide to have the child.

67
00:03:56.000 --> 00:03:57.958
[intense music playing]

68
00:03:58.333 --> 00:04:00.875
-Mommy?
-You're pregnant. honey.

69
00:04:02.125 --> 00:04:03.416
-No!
-Calm down.

70
00:04:03.500 --> 00:04:04.875
We're here to support you.

71
00:04:05.375 --> 00:04:06.833
-It can't be true.
-It is.

72
00:04:06.916 --> 00:04:07.833
No!

73
00:04:08.166 --> 00:04:09.666
-[Clara] It is.
-Hey.

74
00:04:11.458 --> 00:04:12.333
Excuse me.

75
00:04:13.333 --> 00:04:14.500
Blanca!

76
00:04:14.583 --> 00:04:15.625
No. Leave her.

77
00:04:16.708 --> 00:04:18.041
You cannot help. Blanca.

78
00:04:18.666 --> 00:04:19.791
Not like this.

79
00:04:19.875 --> 00:04:21.875
You need to heal first. my dear. Yes?

80
00:04:21.958 --> 00:04:26.041
From here. deep inside you. Be born anew.

81
00:04:26.125 --> 00:04:29.458
[telephone continues ringing]

82
00:04:36.583 --> 00:04:38.958
[theme music playing]

83
00:05:37.708 --> 00:05:40.291
[operator] <i>I'm sorry. sir.</i>
 <i>I've tried many times to connect.</i>

84
00:05:40.375 --> 00:05:41.541
 <i>but they're not answering.</i>

85
00:05:41.625 --> 00:05:42.875
Please try again.

86
00:05:42.958 --> 00:05:47.125
 <i>I'm truly sorry. but we are not allowed</i>
 <i>to keep the line busy for that long.</i>

87
00:05:47.208 --> 00:05:48.208
 <i>Try again later.</i>

88
00:05:50.166 --> 00:05:54.625
[birds chirping]

89
00:06:03.541 --> 00:06:06.083
[operatic music playing]

90
00:06:17.708 --> 00:06:18.958
[woman] Don Esteban.

91
00:06:19.041 --> 00:06:21.666
-The people you asked to see are here.
-I'm coming.

92
00:06:23.333 --> 00:06:26.416
Pedro Tercero García made off
with a large amount of money.

93
00:06:27.208 --> 00:06:29.291
Out of respect
for his father and grandfather.

94
00:06:29.375 --> 00:06:30.750
I haven't filed charges.

95
00:06:30.833 --> 00:06:32.333
But if he doesn't show up.

96
00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:35.250
he'll become a fugitive from justice.

97
00:06:35.333 --> 00:06:37.250
and no one wants him locked up. right?

98
00:06:39.625 --> 00:06:41.208
So I offer a reward to the person

99
00:06:41.291 --> 00:06:43.625
who brings me information
or brings the guy in.

100
00:06:53.916 --> 00:06:55.541
-Tell everyone
-Yes. patron.

101
00:07:06.625 --> 00:07:08.083
I know where Pedro is hiding.

102
00:07:08.166 --> 00:07:10.791
[dark music playing]

103
00:07:13.166 --> 00:07:14.083
I mean it. patron.

104
00:07:14.625 --> 00:07:17.583
Everyone knows where he's hiding. but you.

105
00:07:24.250 --> 00:07:25.583
You'll take me to his hideout.

106
00:07:26.625 --> 00:07:28.458
and if I find out you've been lying.

107
00:07:29.125 --> 00:07:30.541
I'm going to give you a beating.

108
00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:32.583
If I'm right. will you pay up?

109
00:07:36.750 --> 00:07:38.000
[Blanca gasps softly]

110
00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:50.500
[sobs]

111
00:08:05.083 --> 00:08:06.625
Pedro needs to know everything.

112
00:08:14.416 --> 00:08:16.708
[intense music playing]

113
00:08:20.166 --> 00:08:21.291
[Esteban] Is he in there?

114
00:08:21.666 --> 00:08:22.583
[boy] Yes.

115
00:08:39.666 --> 00:08:43.291
[fire crackling]

116
00:09:09.458 --> 00:09:11.250
[gun cocking]

117
00:09:12.833 --> 00:09:16.500
[tense music playing]

118
00:09:54.875 --> 00:09:57.166
[both grunting]

119
00:10:09.125 --> 00:10:11.208
[choking]

120
00:10:29.333 --> 00:10:33.125
[Tercero screams]

121
00:10:38.958 --> 00:10:40.208
Where's my money. patron?

122
00:10:41.833 --> 00:10:43.291
Rats must never get rewarded.

123
00:11:33.791 --> 00:11:34.916
[exhales]

124
00:11:39.000 --> 00:11:40.416
[chuckles softly]

125
00:11:43.833 --> 00:11:45.208
[sighs]

126
00:11:48.875 --> 00:11:49.791
Mm.

127
00:11:53.750 --> 00:11:55.583
-[knock at door]
-[man] Ma'am.

128
00:11:56.125 --> 00:11:57.500
Please wait.

129
00:12:05.750 --> 00:12:06.958
[Clara] What do you see?

130
00:12:07.041 --> 00:12:08.583
[man] There's a bulge on the roof?

131
00:12:08.666 --> 00:12:09.958
Yes. exactly.

132
00:12:10.041 --> 00:12:12.833
A dome that's transparent enough
for light to pass through.

133
00:12:12.916 --> 00:12:14.541
Do you have blueprints for that?

134
00:12:15.083 --> 00:12:16.083
They aren't needed.

135
00:12:16.166 --> 00:12:17.291
I'll explain as you go.

136
00:12:19.250 --> 00:12:21.166
Let's break through this wall.

137
00:12:21.250 --> 00:12:24.416
And if it ends up being bigger.
it's because it was meant to be.

138
00:12:25.041 --> 00:12:26.333
Sure. if you say so.

139
00:12:26.958 --> 00:12:27.875
-Help me.
-Of course.

140
00:12:27.958 --> 00:12:28.833
Thank you.

141
00:12:28.916 --> 00:12:30.791
I don't know how many
new rooms we'll have.

142
00:12:30.875 --> 00:12:33.083
but the rule is that the more the merrier.

143
00:12:33.166 --> 00:12:34.541
The stairs should be over here.

144
00:12:35.416 --> 00:12:37.125
I don't understand. I'm sorry.

145
00:12:38.250 --> 00:12:39.458
It's not difficult.

146
00:12:39.541 --> 00:12:40.416
Allow me.

147
00:12:48.875 --> 00:12:50.791
[thudding continues]

148
00:12:51.750 --> 00:12:52.750
[grunts]

149
00:12:55.375 --> 00:12:56.541
[pants]

150
00:12:58.916 --> 00:13:00.500
Don't worry. it'll be fine.

151
00:13:01.125 --> 00:13:02.625
I'll leave you to it.

152
00:13:02.708 --> 00:13:03.625
Excuse me.

153
00:13:04.333 --> 00:13:06.708
[Alba] <i>Guided by her intuition</i>
 <i>and her spirit friends.</i>

154
00:13:07.416 --> 00:13:10.833
 <i>my grandmother led the transformation</i>
 <i>of the big house on the corner.</i>

155
00:13:11.625 --> 00:13:13.666
 <i>and everyone there joined in to help her.</i>

156
00:13:14.291 --> 00:13:15.791
I brought you more fabric.

157
00:13:15.875 --> 00:13:17.291
Very well. Thank you.

158
00:13:17.500 --> 00:13:19.958
-[debris crashing]
-[all gasp]

159
00:13:22.125 --> 00:13:24.166
[man] I'm sorry. Are you all right?

160
00:13:24.250 --> 00:13:26.041
-Oh. Yes.
-[all laughing]

161
00:13:26.125 --> 00:13:27.208
[Alba] <i>She decided</i>

162
00:13:27.291 --> 00:13:29.750
 <i>that her house would be</i>
 <i>a gathering place and a home</i>

163
00:13:29.833 --> 00:13:33.041
 <i>for everyone willing to join</i>
 <i>in her exploration of the afterlife</i>

164
00:13:33.833 --> 00:13:36.333
 <i>and to help souls in need</i>
 <i>in the world of the living.</i>

165
00:13:36.416 --> 00:13:39.416
I apologize for the mess.
but we will have to make do

166
00:13:39.500 --> 00:13:41.875
until the workers upstairs finish.

167
00:13:41.958 --> 00:13:42.875
Hello.

168
00:13:47.875 --> 00:13:49.541
-Thank you for coming.
-Thank you.

169
00:13:55.583 --> 00:13:56.666
Ceci?

170
00:13:56.750 --> 00:13:57.625
Yes. dear.

171
00:13:57.708 --> 00:13:59.833
-Anything for me?
-No. nothing. Blanquita.

172
00:14:12.875 --> 00:14:15.666
[birds chirping]

173
00:14:16.541 --> 00:14:17.583
Don Esteban.

174
00:14:17.750 --> 00:14:18.958
the mailman has arrived.

175
00:14:19.583 --> 00:14:22.291
I have the latest mail
that arrived for Pedro Tercero.

176
00:14:23.375 --> 00:14:24.291
Thank you.

177
00:14:26.750 --> 00:14:28.791
Pay my friend
and give him a good meal.

178
00:14:28.875 --> 00:14:29.791
Yes. sir.

179
00:14:29.875 --> 00:14:30.791
Come here.

180
00:14:49.875 --> 00:14:52.041
[Alba] <i>My grandfather</i>
 <i>had never felt so alone.</i>

181
00:14:53.291 --> 00:14:56.125
 <i>Not even during his years</i>
 <i>in the mines out in the desert.</i>

182
00:14:57.083 --> 00:14:59.958
 <i>but he had found a way to hear</i>
 <i>about his family's affairs.</i>

183
00:15:00.916 --> 00:15:03.750
 <i>and thus he learned</i>
 <i>he was going to be a grandfather.</i>

184
00:15:07.375 --> 00:15:09.083
[bells chiming]

185
00:15:09.166 --> 00:15:10.958
Is Marga's spirit among us?

186
00:15:19.125 --> 00:15:21.333
I repeat. is Marga's spirit among us?

187
00:15:23.875 --> 00:15:25.333
Why don't you answer?

188
00:15:25.416 --> 00:15:26.916
[indistinct whispering]

189
00:15:27.000 --> 00:15:28.875
I see a sunflower.

190
00:15:29.250 --> 00:15:32.500
Could it be that your daughter
has a sunflower?

191
00:15:33.125 --> 00:15:34.875
She was born at my parents' house.

192
00:15:36.458 --> 00:15:37.583
They had sunflowers.

193
00:15:52.708 --> 00:15:54.833
[Clara] Your daughter
doesn't feel pain anymore.

194
00:15:56.208 --> 00:15:57.833
She says. "Don't be sad.

195
00:15:59.000 --> 00:16:00.500
She's happy in that place.

196
00:16:02.083 --> 00:16:05.833
She wants you to free her
and keep living life.

197
00:16:05.916 --> 00:16:07.458
[woman sobbing]

198
00:16:15.250 --> 00:16:17.958
[Clara] She says that you should
talk to the hummingbird.

199
00:16:19.458 --> 00:16:20.833
That means it's her.

200
00:16:24.666 --> 00:16:28.333
It is her. the hummingbird.
that visits our house.

201
00:16:29.333 --> 00:16:32.041
It's her way to remind you
that she's always with you.

202
00:16:32.125 --> 00:16:35.583
-[somber instrumental music playing]
-[continues sobbing]

203
00:16:48.166 --> 00:16:50.000
[workers chattering]

204
00:16:53.875 --> 00:16:55.416
Are you here to visit Donna Clara?

205
00:16:55.500 --> 00:16:56.958
You're clueless. I'm her husband.

206
00:16:57.041 --> 00:16:58.083
This is my house.

207
00:16:58.166 --> 00:16:59.708
You're Don Esteban. I'm sorry. sir.

208
00:16:59.791 --> 00:17:00.833
I'm new to the house.

209
00:17:01.458 --> 00:17:03.333
Donna Clara is remodeling everything.

210
00:17:15.833 --> 00:17:17.458
Just as I imagined you to be.

211
00:17:17.541 --> 00:17:19.041
[Luisa] I imagined you taller.

212
00:17:19.125 --> 00:17:20.791
-And younger. too.
-[Luisa] Mm.

213
00:17:22.458 --> 00:17:23.375
Good morning.

214
00:17:26.583 --> 00:17:28.041
Clara. I need to talk to you.

215
00:17:30.250 --> 00:17:31.166
Clara.

216
00:17:32.958 --> 00:17:34.083
-Speak to me.
-[Marta] Mm.

217
00:17:34.708 --> 00:17:37.083
[Luisa] Clara will never utter
a word to you again.

218
00:17:39.625 --> 00:17:42.083
-Leave me alone with my wife.
-[Marta] Won't be possible.

219
00:17:42.166 --> 00:17:43.791
Who are you? I don't know any of you.

220
00:17:43.875 --> 00:17:45.375
Nora. Marta and Luisa Mora.

221
00:17:45.500 --> 00:17:47.250
And we go by the Mora sisters.

222
00:17:49.041 --> 00:17:50.375
Clara. let's hash this out.

223
00:17:50.458 --> 00:17:53.500
I don't meddle in your affairs.
but we need to talk about Blanca.

224
00:17:53.583 --> 00:17:55.791
She says she already knows
everything about Blanca.

225
00:17:55.875 --> 00:17:59.291
And the best thing you could do
is go back to the estate. Esteban.

226
00:18:02.875 --> 00:18:03.791
You knew about it?

227
00:18:06.250 --> 00:18:08.041
Turns out I'm the last idiot to find out.

228
00:18:08.125 --> 00:18:11.291
Luisa. this man needs to know
that the only decision about Blanca

229
00:18:11.375 --> 00:18:13.166
that I will respect is what Blanca makes!

230
00:18:13.250 --> 00:18:14.833
-She says--
-I am not deaf!

231
00:18:19.375 --> 00:18:20.958
And her future in the gossip?

232
00:18:22.375 --> 00:18:23.458
What will they say?

233
00:18:33.583 --> 00:18:36.208
[breathing heavily]

234
00:18:40.791 --> 00:18:41.708
There.

235
00:18:42.333 --> 00:18:43.250
Blanca.

236
00:18:45.750 --> 00:18:46.916
Any sudden food urges?

237
00:18:47.000 --> 00:18:48.416
-No. I don't--
-[Esteban] Blanca.

238
00:18:52.416 --> 00:18:53.458
Follow me. Blanca.

239
00:18:57.000 --> 00:18:57.958
[Esteban] Blanca!

240
00:19:02.333 --> 00:19:04.208
I won't let you lay a hand on her again.

241
00:19:06.375 --> 00:19:07.416
Very nice.

242
00:19:09.250 --> 00:19:11.166
I like seeing you stand up for Blanca.

243
00:19:11.666 --> 00:19:12.666
Well. good job.

244
00:19:16.583 --> 00:19:17.625
[grunts]

245
00:19:18.541 --> 00:19:21.166
[intense music playing]

246
00:19:21.500 --> 00:19:22.750
I want the best for you.

247
00:19:25.125 --> 00:19:27.041
And the best for the child on the way.

248
00:19:29.125 --> 00:19:31.333
Jean de Satigny
will give it his last name.

249
00:19:32.666 --> 00:19:34.125
My child has a last name already.

250
00:19:34.208 --> 00:19:35.583
I'm not asking you. Blanca.

251
00:19:36.666 --> 00:19:40.083
You're going to marry the count and move
up north so no one gossips about you.

252
00:19:40.166 --> 00:19:42.333
Blanca. listen.
no one can make you do anything.

253
00:19:42.416 --> 00:19:44.708
We don't want bastards
in the family. damn it!

254
00:19:49.833 --> 00:19:51.791
But I thought we had a bunch of those.

255
00:19:56.625 --> 00:19:58.208
Come with me. Blanca. Let's go.

256
00:19:59.541 --> 00:20:00.375
Please.

257
00:20:00.458 --> 00:20:02.875
I suggest you forget
about that peasant.

258
00:20:07.083 --> 00:20:08.000
I killed him.

259
00:20:14.750 --> 00:20:17.250
I put down that mangy communist dog.

260
00:20:19.958 --> 00:20:21.708
Come with me. Blanca. Let's go.

261
00:20:21.791 --> 00:20:22.708
Stay away.

262
00:20:48.000 --> 00:20:49.166
[Blanca] Please leave.

263
00:20:50.250 --> 00:20:53.125
Blanca? Blanquita. open up.

264
00:20:55.000 --> 00:20:56.250
I wanna be alone!

265
00:20:56.333 --> 00:20:58.250
Blanca. I understand your pain.

266
00:20:59.291 --> 00:21:01.625
but getting married
won't make you feel better.

267
00:21:08.041 --> 00:21:09.291
Blanca. come.

268
00:21:10.041 --> 00:21:10.958
No!

269
00:21:11.833 --> 00:21:12.875
It's already settled.

270
00:21:12.958 --> 00:21:14.458
I'm going to marry the count.

271
00:21:15.375 --> 00:21:17.583
I don't want to see my father ever again.

272
00:21:22.416 --> 00:21:24.500
Blanca. don't ruin your life. please.

273
00:21:27.541 --> 00:21:29.250
I just want you to know one thing.

274
00:21:31.250 --> 00:21:34.916
I will always be here
for whatever you need. no matter what.

275
00:21:38.333 --> 00:21:39.250
[sobs]

276
00:21:39.333 --> 00:21:42.833
[Alba] <i>My grandma had no choice</i>
 <i>but to accept her daughter's decision</i>

277
00:21:42.916 --> 00:21:44.875
 <i>because she knew her very well</i>

278
00:21:44.958 --> 00:21:48.041
 <i>and also knew that</i>
 <i>she wouldn't be able to change her mind.</i>

279
00:21:50.583 --> 00:21:51.958
[man] Congratulations. Count.

280
00:21:52.041 --> 00:21:54.166
-Thank you very much.
-[man] I'm happy for you.

281
00:21:55.375 --> 00:21:57.208
Bianca? Mm.

282
00:21:57.291 --> 00:21:58.291
You have to taste this.

283
00:21:58.375 --> 00:21:59.750
Hey. I'm your husband now.

284
00:22:01.291 --> 00:22:03.458
Yes. sure. Yes. yes.
Can we take a photo. please?

285
00:22:03.541 --> 00:22:04.666
[man 2] Let's do it. Yes.

286
00:22:04.750 --> 00:22:06.208
It's just that it would be better

287
00:22:06.291 --> 00:22:08.458
if the bride was smiling
instead of crying.

288
00:22:11.916 --> 00:22:14.625
Please look over here and now smile.

289
00:22:14.708 --> 00:22:17.041
-There you go. Very good.
-I appreciate it. Thank you.

290
00:22:17.166 --> 00:22:19.000
Esteban. shall we take a photo?

291
00:22:22.250 --> 00:22:24.041
-No. no. no. Blanca!
-[Esteban] Leave her.

292
00:22:24.125 --> 00:22:26.083
Leave her. Jean. She'll get over it.

293
00:22:27.583 --> 00:22:30.666
[intense music playing]

294
00:22:33.250 --> 00:22:36.250
[Alba] <i>The marriage that Blanca</i>
 <i>didn't want was an important event.</i>

295
00:22:37.750 --> 00:22:40.041
 <i>Many noticed the bride</i>
 <i>was in constant tears</i>

296
00:22:40.833 --> 00:22:43.000
 <i>and they assumed it was</i>
 <i>the passion of the moment.</i>

297
00:22:44.250 --> 00:22:46.916
 <i>unaware that she had been crying</i>
 <i>since her father confessed</i>

298
00:22:47.000 --> 00:22:48.958
 <i>to the murder of the love of her life.</i>

299
00:22:49.333 --> 00:22:52.000
-[vibrato intensifying]
-[breathing heavily]

300
00:22:55.750 --> 00:22:56.666
 <i>And yet.</i>

301
00:22:57.416 --> 00:23:01.833
 <i>the ceremony managed to avoid any scandal.</i>
 <i>just like my grandfather had planned.</i>

302
00:23:08.875 --> 00:23:12.333
[slow instrumental music playing]

303
00:23:14.291 --> 00:23:16.125
[sighs]

304
00:23:57.375 --> 00:23:58.458
Ooh!

305
00:24:14.750 --> 00:24:15.875
[car door closes]

306
00:24:19.125 --> 00:24:20.500
Beautiful. right?

307
00:24:24.083 --> 00:24:28.375
[Alba] <i>Only the arid heat of the desert</i>
 <i>was able to dry my mother's tears.</i>

308
00:24:34.041 --> 00:24:39.250
[mystical music playing]

309
00:24:48.500 --> 00:24:49.500
 <i>Bonjour à tous.</i>

310
00:24:53.833 --> 00:24:55.791
Well. is everything in order here?

311
00:24:55.875 --> 00:24:57.708
Everything's in perfect condition. <i>senor.</i>

312
00:24:57.791 --> 00:24:59.208
-Everything's ready.
-Very good.

313
00:24:59.291 --> 00:25:03.375
I'd like you to meet and say hello
to my wife. Blanca de Satigny.

314
00:25:05.041 --> 00:25:08.125
They are Gaspar. Baltazar and Leonor.

315
00:25:09.208 --> 00:25:11.250
Let's go. go get our bags from the car.

316
00:25:11.333 --> 00:25:13.583
and then prepare a welcome
cocktail for this heat.

317
00:25:13.666 --> 00:25:15.375
-Mm-hmm. Yes. signor.
-Come on. quick.

318
00:25:17.750 --> 00:25:19.166
Do you like the house?

319
00:25:19.250 --> 00:25:20.541
I decorated it myself.

320
00:25:22.250 --> 00:25:27.708
A sensitive artist can't help but be moved
by pre-Columbian culture.

321
00:25:30.291 --> 00:25:32.083
Uh! Uh-uh-uh-uh!

322
00:25:32.875 --> 00:25:34.708
[clicks tongue]

323
00:25:35.000 --> 00:25:36.041
Don't touch that.

324
00:25:40.125 --> 00:25:44.083
Ah! Be careful with the sword.
because it's easy to bump into it.

325
00:25:44.166 --> 00:25:45.208
[chuckles]

326
00:25:53.708 --> 00:25:55.750
So what do you think. Blanca?

327
00:25:55.958 --> 00:25:58.291
May I be shown to my bedroom now. Jean?

328
00:25:58.500 --> 00:25:59.750
Sure. In a second.

329
00:25:59.833 --> 00:26:00.750
Just one thing.

330
00:26:03.125 --> 00:26:04.500
-Ah.
-Ah! Ah!

331
00:26:04.583 --> 00:26:05.666
 <i>S'il vous plaît.</i>

332
00:26:06.291 --> 00:26:08.208
[in English] What color is the door?

333
00:26:09.000 --> 00:26:10.291
It's red.

334
00:26:10.375 --> 00:26:11.541
Very good.

335
00:26:11.625 --> 00:26:13.458
And what do you relate to the color red?

336
00:26:14.750 --> 00:26:15.916
-Blood.
-[scoffs]

337
00:26:16.583 --> 00:26:19.083
You're always so dramatic. woman.

338
00:26:19.166 --> 00:26:20.375
Red means stop.

339
00:26:20.458 --> 00:26:22.500
In that room. I built my studio.

340
00:26:22.583 --> 00:26:24.416
Please don't enter there.
because the light

341
00:26:24.500 --> 00:26:27.000
could expose the photos and ruin them.

342
00:26:27.083 --> 00:26:28.000
Perfect.

343
00:26:28.958 --> 00:26:30.958
That means beyond the doors of this house.

344
00:26:31.041 --> 00:26:32.125
we're a married couple.

345
00:26:33.000 --> 00:26:33.916
Behind closed doors.

346
00:26:34.000 --> 00:26:35.791
don't touch me or come into my room.

347
00:26:36.750 --> 00:26:37.666
Wow.

348
00:26:38.916 --> 00:26:39.833
 <i>D'accord.</i>

349
00:26:42.291 --> 00:26:43.208
Excuse me.

350
00:26:46.166 --> 00:26:47.625
I brought all your favorites.

351
00:26:50.875 --> 00:26:54.833
That's the perk of knowing each other
so well after so many years of marriage.

352
00:26:55.708 --> 00:26:56.625
You know.

353
00:26:57.750 --> 00:27:01.791
despite some differences. we've had
a good marriage. and that's undeniable.

354
00:27:03.500 --> 00:27:04.416
Here.

355
00:27:08.958 --> 00:27:10.166
[sighs]

356
00:27:13.083 --> 00:27:14.416
At Las Tres Marías.

357
00:27:14.750 --> 00:27:18.250
I'm not needed as much as I am here.
that's why I'm appointing an administrator

358
00:27:18.333 --> 00:27:19.625
to take care of my estate.

359
00:27:22.458 --> 00:27:24.958
I'd like to use my abilities
for a higher purpose.

360
00:27:29.750 --> 00:27:31.875
I know I can be helpful to my country.

361
00:27:33.333 --> 00:27:38.791
[intense music playing]

362
00:27:41.666 --> 00:27:44.166
I will be announcing
my candidacy for senator.

363
00:27:48.250 --> 00:27:50.791
I hope you'll be proud
of what I'll accomplish.

364
00:27:55.208 --> 00:27:58.458
[Alba] <i>It was inevitable that my grandma</i>
 <i>would think about Rosa's murder</i>

365
00:27:59.041 --> 00:28:02.375
 <i>and her father's decree</i>
 <i>to keep the family away from politics.</i>

366
00:28:02.458 --> 00:28:03.541
[door opens]

367
00:28:12.958 --> 00:28:14.666
[indistinct conversations]

368
00:28:17.625 --> 00:28:19.500
[Jean] This was not my intention.

369
00:28:21.000 --> 00:28:22.958
[laughter]

370
00:28:24.125 --> 00:28:25.666
All right! I lied.

371
00:28:25.750 --> 00:28:27.083
[laughter continues]

372
00:28:33.000 --> 00:28:33.958
[scoffs]

373
00:28:34.208 --> 00:28:35.958
Why are you awake at this hour?

374
00:28:36.166 --> 00:28:37.083
I heard noises.

375
00:28:37.166 --> 00:28:38.166
It's an ancient house.

376
00:28:38.250 --> 00:28:41.125
There are mice. you know. Come on.

377
00:28:41.208 --> 00:28:42.416
Go get some rest.

378
00:28:43.708 --> 00:28:45.375
Go to your room. please.

379
00:28:54.166 --> 00:28:57.083
{\an8}[water splashing softly]

380
00:29:10.083 --> 00:29:11.333
What are you doing there?

381
00:29:14.250 --> 00:29:15.333
Do you need anything?

382
00:29:17.541 --> 00:29:18.458
One minute.

383
00:29:23.958 --> 00:29:25.958
Take it to the post office.
It's for my mom.

384
00:29:30.416 --> 00:29:31.416
My pleasure.

385
00:29:31.916 --> 00:29:35.500
[captivating instrumental music playing]

386
00:29:41.583 --> 00:29:45.583
[Blanca] <i>Dear Mom. why haven't I received</i>
 <i>any letters from you?</i>

387
00:29:46.166 --> 00:29:48.208
 <i>I've already sent you four letters.</i>

388
00:29:49.125 --> 00:29:50.208
 <i>Are you angry at me?</i>

389
00:29:51.583 --> 00:29:55.583
[reading] "This desert can be quite
beautiful and cool at the same time.

390
00:29:55.666 --> 00:29:58.208
Sometimes I think that I'm going crazy.

391
00:29:58.291 --> 00:30:00.083
Everything is strange in this house.

392
00:30:00.166 --> 00:30:01.208
starting with Jean."

393
00:30:02.125 --> 00:30:03.541
[Blanca] <i>I feel very lonely.</i>

394
00:30:04.250 --> 00:30:06.625
 <i>As days go by. my fears continue to grow.</i>

395
00:30:07.333 --> 00:30:09.250
 <i>I don't think I'm going</i>
 <i>to be a good mother.</i>

396
00:30:10.166 --> 00:30:12.041
 <i>I need you so much.</i>

397
00:30:12.291 --> 00:30:13.916
 <i>With love. your daughter.</i>

398
00:30:17.166 --> 00:30:18.583
[Clara] <i>My dear Blanca.</i>

399
00:30:18.666 --> 00:30:21.000
 <i>You can't imagine</i>
 <i>how much I miss you. sweetie.</i>

400
00:30:21.750 --> 00:30:23.250
 <i>Why haven't you written to me?</i>

401
00:30:25.500 --> 00:30:29.375
 <i>The renovation of the house is going well.</i>
 <i>but it's not the same without you.</i>

402
00:30:31.416 --> 00:30:34.708
 <i>The Mora sisters and I have been searching</i>
 <i>for Pedro among the dead.</i>

403
00:30:34.791 --> 00:30:36.708
 <i>but we haven't been able to reach him.</i>

404
00:30:37.958 --> 00:30:39.500
 <i>Trust yourself. sweetie.</i>

405
00:30:39.583 --> 00:30:42.375
 <i>I know you will give your daughter</i>
 <i>everything she needs.</i>

406
00:30:42.833 --> 00:30:44.000
 <i>I love you.</i>

407
00:30:44.791 --> 00:30:45.833
 <i>Please write to me.</i>

408
00:30:47.416 --> 00:30:49.500
[Alba] <i>After months</i>
 <i>without a word from Blanca.</i>

409
00:30:50.916 --> 00:30:52.916
 <i>Clara tried to reach her by other means.</i>

410
00:30:53.666 --> 00:30:55.583
 <i>but telepathy didn't work either.</i>

411
00:30:56.708 --> 00:30:59.666
 <i>and she started to regret</i>
 <i>that she didn't try harder</i>

412
00:30:59.750 --> 00:31:02.500
 <i>to prevent the wedding</i>
 <i>that kept her from her daughter.</i>

413
00:31:03.666 --> 00:31:04.583
Don't worry.

414
00:31:06.208 --> 00:31:07.166
It's all right.

415
00:31:08.416 --> 00:31:11.375
Your daughter is stronger
than she realizes.

416
00:31:17.416 --> 00:31:21.000
[somber instrumental music playing]

417
00:31:22.458 --> 00:31:23.708
[sniffles]

418
00:31:27.458 --> 00:31:29.750
[breathing heavily]

419
00:31:47.375 --> 00:31:48.291
One more. Blanca?

420
00:31:51.458 --> 00:31:52.958
Oh. spectacular.

421
00:31:53.250 --> 00:31:54.125
Enough!

422
00:31:54.583 --> 00:31:56.375
-[camera shutter clicks]
-Please stop.

423
00:31:59.166 --> 00:32:00.208
[clicks]

424
00:32:07.000 --> 00:32:08.000
[clicks]

425
00:32:17.958 --> 00:32:19.541
[Alba] <i>As time slipped away.</i>

426
00:32:19.666 --> 00:32:21.791
 <i>Bianca felt that the loneliness</i>
 <i>of the desert</i>

427
00:32:21.875 --> 00:32:23.625
 <i>was starting to drive her crazy.</i>

428
00:32:24.125 --> 00:32:26.416
 <i>and she looked for a way</i>
 <i>to keep herself busy.</i>

429
00:32:30.291 --> 00:32:33.416
[captivating instrumental music playing]

430
00:32:44.541 --> 00:32:48.166
 <i>Lost in thought and isolated</i>
 <i>from news of the world and her family.</i>

431
00:32:48.250 --> 00:32:51.125
 <i>Blanca wasn't aware</i>
 <i>of the changes that were taking place.</i>

432
00:32:51.875 --> 00:32:55.250
-[baby crying]
-[indistinct chatter]

433
00:32:58.416 --> 00:33:01.500
[Alba] <i>Like my grandmother's joy</i>
 <i>for achieving women's suffrage.</i>

434
00:33:01.583 --> 00:33:02.541
[woman] Yes.

435
00:33:03.833 --> 00:33:06.916
[Alba] <i>Or my grandfather's pride</i>
 <i>at being elected as senator.</i>

436
00:33:17.083 --> 00:33:18.000
Thank you.

437
00:33:22.916 --> 00:33:27.583
[Alba] <i>My mother knew nothing of it.</i>
 <i>abandoned as she was to her in her exile.</i>

438
00:33:40.291 --> 00:33:43.208
[intense music playing]

439
00:33:49.708 --> 00:33:50.541
[grunts]

440
00:33:58.750 --> 00:33:59.666
[pants]

441
00:34:15.333 --> 00:34:16.458
[window slams shut]

442
00:34:20.458 --> 00:34:22.541
[people laughing and chattering]

443
00:34:22.791 --> 00:34:24.458
[Jean] <i>Welcome to my humble house.</i>

444
00:34:24.625 --> 00:34:25.708
[lively music playing]

445
00:34:26.000 --> 00:34:26.875
Oh. come on.

446
00:34:27.125 --> 00:34:28.416
[woman] Yes. cheers. right.

447
00:34:28.875 --> 00:34:31.458
[laughter and chatter continues]

448
00:34:31.666 --> 00:34:32.666
[roars]

449
00:34:37.625 --> 00:34:39.916
Put it on. Blanca! Put it on. Blanca!

450
00:34:40.000 --> 00:34:41.375
Go on! Go on. Blanca!

451
00:34:41.458 --> 00:34:42.458
No!

452
00:34:42.541 --> 00:34:44.041
[Jean] She's a woman of the world.

453
00:34:44.666 --> 00:34:45.875
If you know what I mean.

454
00:34:45.958 --> 00:34:47.583
She's a woman of the world.

455
00:34:47.666 --> 00:34:49.916
Blanca. You must be thrilled.

456
00:34:50.000 --> 00:34:53.750
I mean. it's amazing that your husband
is the count and your father is a senator.

457
00:34:53.833 --> 00:34:54.750
That's amazing.

458
00:34:55.916 --> 00:34:57.000
My father's a senator?

459
00:34:58.833 --> 00:35:00.000
He's a killer. though.

460
00:35:00.083 --> 00:35:01.000
I beg your pardon.

461
00:35:01.083 --> 00:35:04.041
Aren't you the daughter
of the new senator. Esteban Trueba?

462
00:35:05.166 --> 00:35:07.958
[laughing]

463
00:35:08.041 --> 00:35:09.291
What'd you say?

464
00:35:09.708 --> 00:35:11.291
He paid to be a senator?

465
00:35:12.000 --> 00:35:14.208
Blanca! Please don't be tacky.

466
00:35:14.291 --> 00:35:16.666
-We owe your father a lot.
-[man] Wait.

467
00:35:16.750 --> 00:35:20.208
Now that Trueba is a senator.
he will bring better champagne.

468
00:35:20.666 --> 00:35:23.875
[Jean] Yes. for sure.
Why don't we raise a glass to the senator?

469
00:35:24.250 --> 00:35:25.708
 <i>Voila! Sante!</i>

470
00:35:25.791 --> 00:35:26.916
[all laughing]

471
00:35:27.083 --> 00:35:28.500
[Jean] Thanks to the senator.

472
00:35:28.958 --> 00:35:29.875
we're here.

473
00:35:30.250 --> 00:35:32.083
[breathing heavily]

474
00:35:32.166 --> 00:35:33.541
[speaking French] Blanca!

475
00:35:34.791 --> 00:35:35.875
[grunts]

476
00:35:36.625 --> 00:35:39.916
-[in English] I fucking hate this dress!
-It cost an arm and a leg! Blanca!

477
00:35:40.000 --> 00:35:41.291
It's natural silk!

478
00:35:41.375 --> 00:35:42.833
Don't be a killjoy. Jean.

479
00:35:42.958 --> 00:35:45.666
The girl is rich
and she does what she likes!

480
00:35:45.750 --> 00:35:47.541
[all laughing]

481
00:35:47.625 --> 00:35:51.958
-[roaring in frustration]
-[all exclaiming]

482
00:35:54.666 --> 00:35:55.583
[Jean] Blanca!

483
00:35:56.625 --> 00:35:57.666
Hey. Blanca!

484
00:35:58.375 --> 00:35:59.458
Blanca!

485
00:35:59.541 --> 00:36:00.416
[Blanca gasps]

486
00:36:03.875 --> 00:36:05.041
Very well. Blanca.

487
00:36:05.625 --> 00:36:06.541
I give up.

488
00:36:07.791 --> 00:36:10.291
[roaring]

489
00:36:10.375 --> 00:36:14.875
[mystical music playing]

490
00:36:36.708 --> 00:36:37.791
Come here!

491
00:36:40.000 --> 00:36:41.541
I'm right here.

492
00:36:41.791 --> 00:36:43.708
[sobbing]

493
00:36:44.208 --> 00:36:49.125
[enchanting instrumental music playing]

494
00:36:59.083 --> 00:37:02.125
[wind blowing]

495
00:37:43.916 --> 00:37:45.416
[girl echoing] Mom! Mom!

496
00:37:49.875 --> 00:37:50.791
Mom! Mom!

497
00:38:11.375 --> 00:38:14.208
[slow instrumental music playing]

498
00:38:32.125 --> 00:38:34.541
[doors slam]

499
00:38:37.416 --> 00:38:40.500
[man laughing] No!

500
00:38:42.750 --> 00:38:46.458
[people laughing and chattering]

501
00:39:01.291 --> 00:39:06.041
[lively instrumental music playing]

502
00:39:14.250 --> 00:39:15.291
Where were you. huh?

503
00:39:23.666 --> 00:39:24.750
I came to say goodbye.

504
00:39:25.791 --> 00:39:27.875
I told you not to come in.

505
00:39:27.958 --> 00:39:29.833
This is not what you imagined. huh?

506
00:39:30.083 --> 00:39:31.833
This is… this is…

507
00:39:31.916 --> 00:39:35.750
This is art! It's art. pure and simple.

508
00:39:35.833 --> 00:39:38.333
[people laughing]

509
00:39:39.166 --> 00:39:40.708
[Jean] Where are we going. baby?

510
00:39:43.750 --> 00:39:44.958
Blanca. what are you doing?

511
00:39:45.041 --> 00:39:46.875
What are you doing? Blanca. no. wait!

512
00:39:46.958 --> 00:39:48.958
That's. that's too valuable.
Blanca. it's art.

513
00:39:49.041 --> 00:39:50.500
I just told you.

514
00:39:50.583 --> 00:39:51.500
What are you doing?

515
00:39:51.583 --> 00:39:54.041
No! That's. that's too beautiful!

516
00:39:54.791 --> 00:39:56.541
I'll take them so I don't forget.

517
00:39:56.625 --> 00:39:59.625
No. no. no. No. no! No. no. no. no!
No. no. no!

518
00:40:01.166 --> 00:40:02.625
Don't you dare come after me.

519
00:40:23.583 --> 00:40:25.250
[sighing in exhaustion]

520
00:40:27.708 --> 00:40:28.708
[groans]

521
00:40:28.958 --> 00:40:31.041
[train wheels clacking]

522
00:40:31.125 --> 00:40:32.208
[groaning]

523
00:40:34.083 --> 00:40:36.875
[Alba] <i>I was on the verge of being born</i>
 <i>in a narrow gauge train</i>

524
00:40:36.958 --> 00:40:39.083
 <i>at 3:00 p.m. in the middle of the desert.</i>

525
00:40:40.166 --> 00:40:44.125
 <i>but according to my grandma. that would</i>
 <i>have been terrible for my birth chart.</i>

526
00:40:44.208 --> 00:40:45.750
[knocking at door]

527
00:40:47.958 --> 00:40:51.791
And I'm the senator having to open
the front door like a miserable maid.

528
00:40:52.083 --> 00:40:53.333
[knocking at door]

529
00:40:55.375 --> 00:40:58.291
[panting]

530
00:41:03.250 --> 00:41:05.583
[groaning]

531
00:41:08.500 --> 00:41:10.125
[breath trembling]

532
00:41:14.333 --> 00:41:17.833
[Alba] <i>And it was as if all the tears</i>
 <i>my mother held inside</i>

533
00:41:17.916 --> 00:41:20.291
 <i>poured out of her body</i>
 <i>to assist in my birth.</i>

534
00:41:27.500 --> 00:41:32.250
Help me. Mom!

535
00:41:35.000 --> 00:41:40.125
[somber instrumental music playing]

536
00:42:00.166 --> 00:42:05.750
[slow instrumental music playing]

537
